WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.700 --> 00:00:07.700
Every successful Magppie call follows the same eight stages, because each stage does a specific job.

2
00:00:09.500 --> 00:00:17.800
Opening sets the tone and confirms the customer has time. Discovery and qualification tells you who you're talking to.

3
00:00:19.600 --> 00:00:28.100
Problem agitation surfaces the hidden risks of wood kitchens. Solution introduction positions Magppie as the answer.

4
00:00:29.900 --> 00:00:40.233
Product deep dive brings in SilverStone, the safety pillars, and the guarantee. Budget qualification checks alignment before a number is said out loud.

5
00:00:42.033 --> 00:00:51.000
Pricing shares the actual range, followed by a check-in question. And WhatsApp handoff turns the conversation into a next step.

6
00:00:52.800 --> 00:01:00.200
Skipping a stage, especially jumping straight to pricing, is the single most common way a good call goes wrong.

7
00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:06.500
Eight stages. From hello to handoff.

